Title: Object: Women of Caramania
Series: Views in Egypt, Palestine and other parts of the Ottoman Empire
Description: Plate 13 in volume III: a woman with a white veil which covers her face, holding a sleeping baby in her arms, walking to left; a child by her side, holding a tray; three women at the entrance of a building on the left, another woman seated at bottom of the steps; after Mayer; published state. 1803 Hand-coloured aquatint with etching
Bibliographic references: Abbey Travel / Travel in Aquatint and lithography 1770-1860 from the library of J.R.Abbey (369.III.13)
